    {
      "id": "0d5b70b56a5c02c92c5cf8f9469c84e2c6c3ae3c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-11-04 23:36:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis gives the misleading impression that the fsname is part of the MGS name, when it is not. Also, this has implications for interoperability, since old devices and Lustre versions will expect the device name to be \"MGS\".  It may also cause problems with filesystem monitoring tools.  \n\nThis seems to me to be the wrong type of fix for the problem at hand. It is introducing interoperability problems for what appears to be a recently added defect in the code. I'd prefer to fix the code than to change the device name.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e2728a8809f042485db743a65557c03e77bd7431",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2014-11-05 00:20:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYour right. This would break interop. Working on another solution.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
